workflow.name: Sync lead replies from Google Sheets to GHL CRM & create ClickUp follow-up tasks
workflow.description:
## Description
Keep your CRM and task system perfectly in sync ‚Äî automatically. This workflow monitors a Google Sheet for lead reply updates, instantly updates the corresponding contact in GoHighLevel (GHL), and creates a ClickUp follow-up task when a response is detected. It ensures your sales team never misses a warm lead and every reply is logged, tracked, and acted upon. ‚ö°

## What This Template Does
- Watches a Google Sheet for reply status changes (‚ÄúYes‚Äù in the Replied column). üìÑ
- Filters only rows where a lead has replied. üîç
- Updates the corresponding contact record in GoHighLevel (GHL). üîó
- Automatically creates a follow-up task in ClickUp with lead details. üóÇÔ∏è
- Merges updates from both GHL and ClickUp into a single result. üîÑ
- Logs sync status and timestamps in a tracking sheet (Sheet2) for auditing. üìã

## Key Benefits
- Instant sync: Update GHL and ClickUp the moment a lead replies. ‚öôÔ∏è
- Zero manual work: Automated updates and follow-up task creation. üö´
- Full traceability: Audit trail stored in a second Google Sheet. ‚úÖ
- Increased sales responsiveness: Teams act immediately on new replies. üí¨
- Multi-app harmony: Connects Google Sheets, GHL, and ClickUp seamlessly. üåê

## Features
- Google Sheets trigger runs every minute to check for changes. ‚è±Ô∏è
- Conditional logic (If node) processes only ‚ÄúReplied = Yes‚Äù leads. ‚úÖ
- GHL contact update node for CRM synchronization. üíº
- ClickUp task creation node with customizable priority and naming. üìù
- Merge node to unify both paths before final sheet update. üîÄ
- Timestamp and action tracking for audit clarity. üìä
- Visual sticky notes explaining each stage. üß©

## Requirements
- n8n instance (cloud or self-hosted). üß∞
- Google Sheet with headers: Name, GHL_ID, Replied, Email. üìë
- Connected credentials for:
- Google Sheets API (Trigger + Update access)
- GoHighLevel OAuth2 API
- ClickUp API
- Separate ‚Äúlog‚Äù sheet (Sheet2) for sync tracking. üìÑ

## Target Audience
- Sales teams using GoHighLevel for CRM and ClickUp for task management. üéØ
- Agencies managing multiple client pipelines. ü§ù
- Business development reps who track lead replies manually. üìû
- Founders automating lead follow-up and CRM hygiene. üöÄ

## Step-by-Step Setup Instructions (Concise)
- Prepare a Google Sheet with columns: Name, GHL_ID, Email, Replied. üìã
- Add a second sheet (‚ÄúSheet2‚Äù) for tracking updates. üìä
- Connect credentials for Google Sheets, GoHighLevel, and ClickUp in n8n. üîê
- Import and open this workflow.
- Update GHL contact field mappings if your CRM structure differs. ‚öôÔ∏è
- Adjust ClickUp team, space, and list IDs to match your setup. üìÇ
- Execute manually once for testing, then enable it to run every minute. ‚ñ∂Ô∏è

## Security Best Practices
- Share your Google Sheet only with the n8n Google account (Editor). üîí
- Keep API credentials securely stored in n8n‚Äôs credential manager. üõ°Ô∏è
- Log timestamps for traceability and rollback. ‚è≥
- Periodically archive older sync logs to keep the sheet lightweight. üßπ

parameters.content:
## üîÑ Auto-Sync Workflow

**Purpose:** Automatically syncs lead reply status from Google Sheets to GoHighLevel (GHL) and creates follow-up tasks.

**Runs:** Every minute

**What happens:**
1. Monitors Sheet for replies
2. Updates GHL contact records
3. Creates ClickUp tasks
4. Marks sync status in Sheet

## üëÄ Step 1: Watch for Changes

Monitors Google Sheet every minute for new/updated rows.

**Triggers when:**
- New row added
- Existing row updated
- 'Replied' column changes

**Expected columns:**
- Name
- GHL_ID
- Replied (Yes/No)
- Email

*Checks: Every 60 seconds*

## üîç Step 2: Filter Leads

Checks if 'Replied' column = 'Yes'

**TRUE path:** Lead replied ‚Üí Continue processing

**FALSE path:** No reply ‚Üí Stop (do nothing)

*Only processes leads who have responded*

## üîÄ Split Processing

Workflow branches into TWO parallel paths:

**Path A (TRUE - Top):**
Updates GoHighLevel contact

**Path B (FALSE - Bottom):**
Creates ClickUp follow-up task

*Both paths run simultaneously*

## üìä Path A: Update GHL

Updates contact in GoHighLevel CRM.

**Uses:** GHL_ID from sheet

**Updates:**
- Contact status
- Custom fields
- Last activity timestamp

*Keeps GHL database in sync*

## ‚úèÔ∏è Mark GHL Complete

Adds tracking fields:

**Next_Step:** "GHL Updated ‚úì"
**Sync_Timestamp:** Current date/time

*Prepares data for sheet update*

## ‚úÖ Path B: Create Task

Creates ClickUp task for follow-up.

**Task includes:**
- Lead name
- Reply notification
- Contact details
- GHL ID reference
- Priority: High

*Ensures timely follow-up*

## ‚úèÔ∏è Mark Task Complete

Adds tracking fields:

**Next_Step:** "ClickUp Task Created ‚úì"
**Sync_Timestamp:** Current date/time

*Prepares data for sheet update*

## üîó Step 3: Merge Results

Combines data from both paths:
- GHL update status
- ClickUp task status
- Timestamps

**Result:** Single data stream with all updates

*Ready for final sheet update*

## üìù Step 4: Update Sheet

Writes sync results to Sheet2.

**Matches by:** GHL_ID

**Updates columns:**
- Next_Step (action taken)
- Sync_Timestamp (when)
- Sync_Status ("Completed")

**Purpose:** Audit trail & prevents duplicate processing

*Workflow complete! ‚ú®*

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
